1
00:00:11,250 --> 00:00:14,458
Look... Just hear
me out, please...

2
00:00:14,541 --> 00:00:19,833
I know it's hard to believe,
but... you really were a dude.

3
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:28,666
Why do you keep saying that?

4
00:00:28,750 --> 00:00:30,208
No, no, no. Don't cry...

5
00:00:30,291 --> 00:00:32,250
I promise you, I'm not
trying to be mean...

6
00:00:32,333 --> 00:00:35,958
I'm doing this for Mayuri.

7
00:00:36,041 --> 00:00:37,708
I need you to find
it within yourself

8
00:00:37,791 --> 00:00:39,458
to give up being a girl.

9
00:02:25,375 --> 00:02:26,791
What's the damage...?

10
00:02:26,875 --> 00:02:29,708
You're sitting there, like...
well... like an apprentice

11
00:02:29,791 --> 00:02:32,291
who screwed up yakisoba
noodles in front of the chef.

12
00:02:32,375 --> 00:02:34,708
Thank you... That's
not a bad analogy...

13
00:02:34,791 --> 00:02:36,208
Well done...

14
00:02:36,291 --> 00:02:37,916
Guess I prefer that to being
told I look like a busboy...

15
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:41,416
'Course could've gone the other
way with it... called me noodle.

16
00:02:42,791 --> 00:02:44,458
Well hey, at least you
still have the gumption

17
00:02:44,541 --> 00:02:46,708
to wring a bad joke
out of the situation.

18
00:02:46,791 --> 00:02:50,500
Okarin! I am so mad at you right
now I can hardly see straight!

19
00:02:50,583 --> 00:02:52,041
Wha... What are
you talking about?

20
00:02:52,125 --> 00:02:54,000
Don't you even try to
play all innocent...!

21
00:02:54,083 --> 00:02:55,916
You made Ruka cry!

22
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,333
How do you know that?!

23
00:02:57,416 --> 00:02:59,375
I kind of put it together
when I invited her

24
00:02:59,458 --> 00:03:01,416
to the lab today and
she burst into tears...

25
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:04,000
I asked what was wrong--you
know, like friends do--

26
00:03:04,083 --> 00:03:06,583
and she told me
you called her a boy!

27
00:03:06,666 --> 00:03:09,666
She didn't happen to
mention the D-mail, did she?

28
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:11,166
What's that got to do...?

29
00:03:11,250 --> 00:03:13,416
Stop trying to worm your
way out of this, mister...!

30
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:16,541
You owe Ruka an apology
and that's all there is to it!

31
00:03:19,625 --> 00:03:22,208
You jerk.

32
00:03:22,291 --> 00:03:23,916
You don't say things
like that to a lady,

33
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:24,875
what's wrong with you?

34
00:03:24,958 --> 00:03:26,375
Don't jump to conclusions...!

35
00:03:26,458 --> 00:03:28,000
There's method
to my crassness!

36
00:03:28,083 --> 00:03:29,375
Of course there is.

37
00:03:29,458 --> 00:03:31,250
If I may speak with you
in private... I'll clarify.

38
00:03:31,333 --> 00:03:34,916
Damn it! Would you quit it
with the jacket already!?

39
00:03:38,416 --> 00:03:40,208
That's the long and
short of it, really.

40
00:03:40,291 --> 00:03:43,791
The next D-mail I have to
undo is the one we let Ruka send

41
00:03:43,875 --> 00:03:46,750
to his mother's pager while
she was pregnant with him.

42
00:03:46,833 --> 00:03:50,250
So, Urushibara
really is a boy...

43
00:03:50,333 --> 00:03:51,791
That's rather hard to take in.

44
00:03:51,875 --> 00:03:55,750
Well, believe me, it's the
truth... At least it used to be.

45
00:03:55,833 --> 00:03:59,166
But she's so... feminine...

46
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:01,541
Next you'll tell me
she looked like Hashida.

47
00:04:08,333 --> 00:04:11,000
Ooooh. No.

48
00:04:11,083 --> 00:04:13,541
Heh. look-wise, Ruka's no
different than he is now.

49
00:04:13,625 --> 00:04:14,875
Whew. Okay, then.

50
00:04:14,958 --> 00:04:17,500
Anyway... Point is, if
we intend to save Mayuri,

51
00:04:17,583 --> 00:04:19,625
we have to persuade Ruka
to go back to being a boy.

52
00:04:19,708 --> 00:04:21,541
Think about it, though:
is it necessary...?

53
00:04:21,625 --> 00:04:23,500
In this case you know
what the text said,

54
00:04:23,583 --> 00:04:25,625
so you can undo it without
her being a part of it...

55
00:04:25,708 --> 00:04:28,833
A little underhanded maybe, but
it might spare some feelings...

56
00:04:28,916 --> 00:04:30,916
I don't think Ruka could
ever be "persuaded..."

57
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,500
The problem with
that scenario is

58
00:04:32,583 --> 00:04:34,666
that I haven't the first clue as
to his mother's pager number...

59
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:37,833
Besides... I'd really rather
not resort to cheap trickery...

60
00:04:37,916 --> 00:04:40,458
We're playing with another
human being's identity here;

61
00:04:40,541 --> 00:04:41,500
I don't want to be clever.

62
00:04:41,583 --> 00:04:43,083
Good luck upholding
those principles

63
00:04:43,166 --> 00:04:45,000
without reducing her to tears.

64
00:04:45,083 --> 00:04:48,250
You're just joking
around with me, right?

65
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:50,625
'Course you are...
That's what you do.

66
00:04:50,708 --> 00:04:53,666
There is such a thing
as taking things too far,

67
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:55,875
though; in case no one told you!

68
00:04:58,208 --> 00:05:00,875
That didn't hurt for the
reasons you think it did.

69
00:05:00,958 --> 00:05:03,083
What? I don't follow...

70
00:05:03,166 --> 00:05:05,083
I was just trying to be as
straightforward as possible...

71
00:05:05,166 --> 00:05:07,583
It's not like I told him he
was hideously deformed.

72
00:05:07,666 --> 00:05:09,166
She's in love with you,
you moron...!

73
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:11,875
You might as well have told the
poor thing she was Quasimodo.

74
00:05:11,958 --> 00:05:13,208
Whoa, whoa, whoa...

75
00:05:13,291 --> 00:05:15,208
Stop...! Put yourself
in her place for a minute.

76
00:05:15,291 --> 00:05:17,208
How would you feel under
the circumstances...?

77
00:05:17,291 --> 00:05:19,791
Essentially sexless to
the person you desire.

78
00:05:19,875 --> 00:05:23,250
But, he's... What am I supposed
to do? He really is a guy!

79
00:05:23,333 --> 00:05:26,083
In another world-line
maybe, but not in this one.

80
00:05:32,166 --> 00:05:34,375
He-- <i>she</i> --wants to talk to me.

81
00:05:34,458 --> 00:05:37,000
Could you come by the shrine
when you have a chance?

82
00:05:39,625 --> 00:05:41,041
Hi, Okabe.

83
00:05:41,125 --> 00:05:43,291
Uh, so yeah.
Sorry about earlier.

84
00:05:43,375 --> 00:05:46,833
No... I'm sorry for
getting so emotional.

85
00:05:46,916 --> 00:05:49,666
Water under the bridge.
You wanted to talk?

86
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:53,416
Um, yes... I kind of had
a favor I wanted to ask.

87
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:54,708
By all means.

88
00:05:54,791 --> 00:05:56,958
Okay, I'll just come
right out with it:

89
00:05:57,041 --> 00:06:00,875
I believe you... So... well...

90
00:06:00,958 --> 00:06:02,333
Yeah?

91
00:06:02,416 --> 00:06:07,291
I'll agree to go back to
being a boy if... if... oh...

92
00:06:07,375 --> 00:06:09,708
If you'll be my boyfriend!

93
00:06:10,958 --> 00:06:15,583
I'm sorry...?!
I don't, uh... Why me?!

94
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:17,916
Because I like you.

95
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:21,291
More than that:
I'm crazy about you.

96
00:06:21,375 --> 00:06:22,750
All I...

97
00:06:22,833 --> 00:06:24,750
All I want out of this is
to be with you for a day...

98
00:06:24,833 --> 00:06:27,875
Just one day... Give me
that before I change back!

99
00:06:27,958 --> 00:06:31,500
But... You're a dude... I...

100
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:35,791
Okay, okay: yes! Done deal!

101
00:06:35,875 --> 00:06:38,291
Just stop crying...!
So be it...!

102
00:06:38,375 --> 00:06:40,375
I'll take one for the
team, if only for day!

103
00:06:40,458 --> 00:06:42,208
Let us be an item!

104
00:06:42,291 --> 00:06:43,666
You really mean that?

105
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:45,041
Uh, the waterworks...

106
00:06:45,125 --> 00:06:48,291
I'm sorry... I'm just so happy.

107
00:06:50,416 --> 00:06:52,500
Unexpectedly touching...

108
00:06:53,541 --> 00:06:55,208
So the only way
through this is for you

109
00:06:55,291 --> 00:06:57,416
to go on a date
with her tomorrow?

110
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:59,541
That's correct.

111
00:06:59,625 --> 00:07:01,750
Bleh. A mad scientist
and a high schooler...

112
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:03,833
Pardon my flesh
for crawling a little.

113
00:07:03,916 --> 00:07:06,958
Ha ha... I realize
I'm throwing caution

114
00:07:07,041 --> 00:07:08,708
to the wind by coming to my
assistant for dating advice,

115
00:07:08,791 --> 00:07:10,416
but that's no
reason to taunt me.

116
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:12,000
