242
00:12:21,750 --> 00:12:23,750
Okabe!

243
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:25,500
I'm so sorry!

244
00:12:26,666 --> 00:12:29,083
I thought I'd given myself
plenty of time to get here...

245
00:12:29,166 --> 00:12:31,625
I, uh... hope you
haven't waited long.

246
00:12:31,708 --> 00:12:35,791
No, no... I... Just got
here myself, actually.

247
00:12:35,875 --> 00:12:38,375
Whew, oh good...
So I'm not late.

248
00:12:40,875 --> 00:12:43,375
So ... Shall we go?

249
00:12:43,458 --> 00:12:44,916
Sure!

250
00:12:53,708 --> 00:12:55,791
I've never seen you out
of your lab coat before;

251
00:12:55,875 --> 00:12:57,125
you look really sharp.

252
00:12:57,208 --> 00:12:59,833
Well... this being a
special occasion and all...

253
00:13:00,833 --> 00:13:02,083
"When walking down the street,

254
00:13:02,166 --> 00:13:04,666
take the side of oncoming
traffic, but be subtle."

255
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:06,333
Something's
bothering you, isn't it?

256
00:13:06,416 --> 00:13:09,541
No, not at all!
I'm just... thinking.

257
00:13:09,625 --> 00:13:11,833
Oh my! What on earth is that?!

258
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:13,958
At least his heart's
in the right place.

259
00:13:14,041 --> 00:13:15,708
"Causally-delicately--shield her

260
00:13:15,791 --> 00:13:18,166
from any passing cars
and/or motorcycles."

261
00:13:18,250 --> 00:13:19,333
Fire in the hole!

262
00:13:19,416 --> 00:13:21,458
Atta boy!

263
00:13:21,541 --> 00:13:22,791
Okabe...

264
00:13:22,875 --> 00:13:23,666
Oww...

265
00:13:23,750 --> 00:13:25,375
Are you two alright?

266
00:13:25,458 --> 00:13:27,875
Don't accept help from
a maid, damn it all...!

267
00:13:27,958 --> 00:13:29,583
A girl doesn't want to
see her man touching

268
00:13:29,666 --> 00:13:32,666
some frilly little chit and
don't take her tissue pack!

269
00:13:32,750 --> 00:13:36,208
Is it me, or are you gettin' a
vicarious thrill from all this?

270
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:42,416
So, the weather sure
is nice today, huh?

271
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:45,583
Yeah...

272
00:13:45,666 --> 00:13:47,583
It is partially cloudy, though.

273
00:13:47,666 --> 00:13:49,083
Yeah, I guess.

274
00:13:54,666 --> 00:13:57,500
The cake is really good.
Not too rich...

275
00:13:57,583 --> 00:14:00,208
Yes. I'm liking the coffee, too.

276
00:14:04,375 --> 00:14:05,750
What is wrong with me...?!

277
00:14:05,833 --> 00:14:08,291
I'm a master of small talk,
especially around Ruka...

278
00:14:08,375 --> 00:14:10,166
Why does dating
change the dynamic?!

279
00:14:10,250 --> 00:14:11,625
How did you find this place...?

280
00:14:11,708 --> 00:14:13,500
I assume you must be a regular.

281
00:14:13,583 --> 00:14:15,166
No...!

282
00:14:15,250 --> 00:14:16,458
This is a shipwreck...

283
00:14:16,541 --> 00:14:18,000
"The key to good conversation

284
00:14:18,083 --> 00:14:20,166
is treating it like
a game of catch."

285
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:23,666
This is actually
my first time here.

286
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:24,875
He tossed it back!

287
00:14:24,958 --> 00:14:26,416
And on the subject of firsts...

288
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:27,875
Today being August fourteenth,

289
00:14:27,958 --> 00:14:29,875
this is the anniversary of
the first patent ever issued

290
00:14:29,958 --> 00:14:32,000
in the country of Japan.
Isn't that fascinating?

291
00:14:32,083 --> 00:14:33,916
Yeah, tossed it
back into the pit!

292
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:36,458
You're like an
encyclopedia of neat stuff.

293
00:14:36,541 --> 00:14:38,666
Hmm? Well you know how it is.

294
00:14:43,916 --> 00:14:45,750
Can we please get the
hell out of here now...?

295
00:14:45,833 --> 00:14:47,833
It's not like we can just
bust through the window

296
00:14:47,916 --> 00:14:49,916
on zip lines and rescue him...

297
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:53,208
We're not going anywhere until
we've seen this thing through.

298
00:14:53,291 --> 00:14:54,791
Thank you. Come again.

299
00:14:57,541 --> 00:14:59,583
Umm... Are you bored?

300
00:14:59,666 --> 00:15:01,125
I mean with the
whole date thing...?

301
00:15:01,208 --> 00:15:03,208
I'd understand... It's okay.

302
00:15:03,291 --> 00:15:04,750
Don't be ridiculous,
of course not...!

303
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:07,458
I was just marshalling my
strength for phase two...!

304
00:15:07,541 --> 00:15:08,916
Come along!

305
00:15:12,333 --> 00:15:14,041
Ruka?

306
00:15:14,125 --> 00:15:17,458
This heat is killing me...

307
00:15:19,166 --> 00:15:21,083
He just walked straight
to Ueno and back!

308
00:15:21,166 --> 00:15:22,125
What the hell?

309
00:15:27,750 --> 00:15:30,166
Hey, Okabe...

310
00:15:30,250 --> 00:15:32,458
Do you remember the first
time the two of us met...?

311
00:15:32,541 --> 00:15:35,041
That amazingly chivalrous
stunt you pulled?

312
00:15:36,625 --> 00:15:39,000
Those wannabe paparazzi
were swarming all over me

313
00:15:39,083 --> 00:15:40,208
with their cameras and stuff.

314
00:15:40,291 --> 00:15:41,541
I was terrified

315
00:15:41,625 --> 00:15:44,583
and you jumped in to defend
a complete stranger.

316
00:15:44,666 --> 00:15:46,083
Oh. Yeah.

317
00:15:49,416 --> 00:15:51,750
I... I can't even
begin to thank you...!

318
00:15:51,833 --> 00:15:54,583
Sorry for all the trouble.

319
00:15:54,666 --> 00:15:57,041
Hm? Why are you apologizing?

320
00:15:57,125 --> 00:15:59,291
Because I look like a girl...

321
00:15:59,375 --> 00:16:05,750
People always make
a big deal out of it.

322
00:16:05,833 --> 00:16:07,541
What you look like is
neither here nor there...

323
00:16:07,625 --> 00:16:09,833
People are idiots.

324
00:16:09,916 --> 00:16:13,041
The genuine you...
transcends that rot.

325
00:16:13,125 --> 00:16:15,916
You have no idea what hearing
those words meant to me then.

326
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:18,541
For the first time
I felt like a real person.

327
00:16:18,625 --> 00:16:23,083
It stuck with me...
Made me fall for you...

328
00:16:23,166 --> 00:16:25,666
Hey... You'd have heard it
from someone eventually...

329
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:29,625
I... Wait! You
remember all that?!

330
00:16:29,708 --> 00:16:32,416
But that comes from when you
were a guy, doesn't it?!

331
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:36,375
Well... I... That...
shouldn't make sense,

332
00:16:36,458 --> 00:16:40,166
but I guess so...
I'm suddenly confused...

333
00:16:40,250 --> 00:16:42,416
This is exactly what
happened to Faris...

334
00:16:43,625 --> 00:16:46,333
Her memories are reaching
across conflicting world-lines.

335
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:54,583
Thank you... It was
sweet of you to do this.

336
00:16:54,666 --> 00:16:57,625
Having you for my
boyfriend, even... for a day...

337
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,583
It was... It meant
everything to me...

338
00:17:02,666 --> 00:17:03,666
Hey...

339
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:06,458
Here. My mother's
old pager number.

340
00:17:16,708 --> 00:17:21,333
"Meat veg. Meat meat
veg. Meat veg meat. Veg."

341
00:17:21,416 --> 00:17:23,666
That ought make Urushibara's
mom take the first message

342
00:17:23,750 --> 00:17:25,041
with a big grain of salt.

343
00:17:25,125 --> 00:17:26,958
She'll discount the
whole thing as a prank.

344
00:17:27,041 --> 00:17:29,958
I think we're
ready to fire it off.

345
00:17:31,916 --> 00:17:34,250
What's wrong, Okabe...?
You look a little...

346
00:17:34,333 --> 00:17:37,416
Too-too-roo!
Great news, you guys...!

347
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:40,833
I saw Ruka out on a date with a
tall, dark man of mystery today!

348
00:17:40,916 --> 00:17:42,333
How awesome
heart-warming is that?!

349
00:17:42,416 --> 00:17:44,875
Uh... Yeah, she
was with Okabe.

350
00:17:44,958 --> 00:17:46,416
What? Nuh-uh...!

351
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:49,958
This guy was wearing clothes
he wouldn't be caught dead in.

352
00:17:50,041 --> 00:17:51,458
There was just this aura
about him, you know?

353
00:17:51,541 --> 00:17:54,500
Total gentleman. Definitely
not someone we've ever met.

354
00:17:54,583 --> 00:17:55,958
Exactly!

355
00:17:56,041 --> 00:17:57,625
That wasn't the
real me out there...!

356
00:17:57,708 --> 00:18:01,541
Ruka was duped by a figment of
our imagination; a mere charade!

357
00:18:01,625 --> 00:18:02,708
What happened?

358
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:08,166
Our date isn't over yet.

359
00:18:08,250 --> 00:18:09,750
Wait, what? Okabe...

360
00:18:09,833 --> 00:18:13,541
Kyouma...! How dare you
saddle me with that insult!

361
00:18:13,625 --> 00:18:16,166
And enough of the boyfriend/
girlfriend, shemale shtick!

362
00:18:16,250 --> 00:18:20,083
Prattling on about gender roles;
hell, I wasn't born yesterday!

363
00:18:20,166 --> 00:18:21,875
The only thing that
matters is chemistry...!

364
00:18:21,958 --> 00:18:24,416
Everything else
is a non-issue...

365
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,083
I'm the guru.
You're the grunt...

366
00:18:26,166 --> 00:18:27,666
That's how it's
always been with us...

367
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:31,541
That is how it's always
going to be... Understood?

368
00:18:34,125 --> 00:18:35,375
Yes sir!

369
00:18:35,458 --> 00:18:37,250
Then showcase what you've
learned from knowing me!

370
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:39,583
Take up Samidare!

371
00:18:39,666 --> 00:18:41,166
Excellent!

372
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:42,083
Don't falter! Keep it up!

373
00:18:42,166 --> 00:18:44,541
Right!

374
00:18:44,625 --> 00:18:47,166
Heed me, grasshoppa.
You have much to learn...

375
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:48,416
Stories of this blade's

376
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:50,500
supernatural proclivities
are notorious...

377
00:18:50,583 --> 00:18:53,416
Many of them traceable
to Yoshitsune's time.

378
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:55,458
The most gnomic
and profound of these

379
00:18:55,541 --> 00:18:57,625
tells of a wandering samurai,
lost beneath the--

380
00:18:57,708 --> 00:18:59,250
This is officially a disaster.

381
00:18:59,333 --> 00:19:00,666
Oh stop it, silly...!

382
00:19:00,750 --> 00:19:04,541
Look how much they're
enjoying each other's company!

383
00:19:04,625 --> 00:19:06,708
I think our work
here is done, people.

384
00:19:11,958 --> 00:19:13,500
Promise me you'll save her...

385
00:19:13,583 --> 00:19:16,625
Do whatever you have to.

386
00:19:16,708 --> 00:19:17,958
I think I might know
what happened

387
00:19:18,041 --> 00:19:20,166
to that old PC you've
been looking for.

388
00:19:20,250 --> 00:19:22,541
The 5100?!

389
00:19:22,625 --> 00:19:25,625
We had a computer from the
seventies that I kind of

390
00:19:25,708 --> 00:19:28,416
maybe knocked over and broke
while going through storage.

391
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:31,500
But... it was a total
accident...I didn't know!

392
00:19:31,583 --> 00:19:33,958
It was just another piece
of junk thrown into the mix...

393
00:19:34,041 --> 00:19:36,875
I'm so sorry!

394
00:19:36,958 --> 00:19:39,041
It's my fault... I'm an idiot...

395
00:19:39,125 --> 00:19:43,708
But you've got to find a
way around it and save her!

396
00:19:43,791 --> 00:19:45,708
Thank you for training
with me like we used to

397
00:19:45,791 --> 00:19:47,041
in the old days;

398
00:19:47,125 --> 00:19:50,666
it meant more to me than
I think you'll ever know.

399
00:19:50,750 --> 00:19:51,833
I...

400
00:19:51,916 --> 00:19:55,083
Please go... I don't
want to cry again...

401
00:19:55,166 --> 00:19:56,500
You've seen me do it enough.

402
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,208
Hey! Aren't you
forgetting something?

403
00:20:02,291 --> 00:20:07,333
The password...
El... Psy... Congree.

404
00:20:07,416 --> 00:20:08,541
Congroo.

405
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:12,500
Sure... Whatever.

406
00:20:15,708 --> 00:20:19,500
I... I really don't want
to do this... It's so...

407
00:20:19,583 --> 00:20:22,916
I mean... The second
I give up being a girl,

408
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,250
I'll have to bury
my feelings for you

409
00:20:24,333 --> 00:20:25,333
the way I've always done!

410
00:20:25,416 --> 00:20:27,750
It's not fair!

411
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:29,625
I'm not allowed to
like you if I'm a boy!

412
00:20:29,708 --> 00:20:33,583
People won't understand...

413
00:20:33,666 --> 00:20:34,916
Rukako...

414
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,750
The thing is I could
handle all that

415
00:20:36,833 --> 00:20:39,500
if I was just allowed
to remember how
wonderful today's been...

416
00:20:39,583 --> 00:20:41,791
But this'll all go away...

417
00:20:41,875 --> 00:20:44,375
I'll have no idea that you
and I actually went on a date...

418
00:20:44,458 --> 00:20:48,125
That I got to hold you
like this without worrying

419
00:20:48,208 --> 00:20:51,000
what everyone
else would think...

420
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:52,625
God, if I'd known being a girl

421
00:20:52,708 --> 00:20:54,125
would hurt this
much in the long run,

422
00:20:54,208 --> 00:20:55,291
I wouldn't have changed...!

423
00:20:55,375 --> 00:20:57,958
Why did I do this to myself?!

424
00:20:58,041 --> 00:20:59,500
Listen to me, damn it!

425
00:20:59,583 --> 00:21:02,166
What you are doesn't matter.
It's who you are...!

426
00:21:02,250 --> 00:21:06,250
Nothing's going to
change between us!

427
00:21:06,333 --> 00:21:07,666
When you say it like that...

428
00:21:07,750 --> 00:21:09,625
I can almost believe you...

429
00:21:09,708 --> 00:21:11,875
And I'll have the first
thing you said to me...

430
00:21:11,958 --> 00:21:13,875
That should be enough.

431
00:21:13,958 --> 00:21:15,916
Just do me one
more favor, okay...?

432
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:19,041
Remember when
I was a girl...

433
00:21:19,125 --> 00:21:22,666
Remember how different
things might've been.

434
00:21:22,750 --> 00:21:26,541
I... won't be able to help it.

435
00:21:34,541 --> 00:21:36,833
Why are you standing
there like that?

436
00:21:39,250 --> 00:21:42,541
Urushibara Ruka...
Delicate as an orchid.

437
00:21:42,625 --> 00:21:43,958
Fair as a cherry blossom...

438
00:21:44,041 --> 00:21:46,666
The personification
of feminine grace.

439
00:21:46,750 --> 00:21:48,750
Hey, uh... Question.

440
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:49,958
Yeah?

441
00:21:50,041 --> 00:21:52,416
Do you... Like me?

442
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:54,333
Where's this coming from?!

443
00:21:54,416 --> 00:21:55,541
Do you?

444
00:21:55,625 --> 00:22:00,958
Kyouma, please...
I... I respect you.

445
00:22:01,041 --> 00:22:03,583
And... a dude.

446
00:22:12,625 --> 00:22:16,250
One more D-mail... Deep breath.

